## 🛡️ PRE-COMMIT HOOKS (Enforced)

```bash
# .husky/pre-commit
#!/bin/sh
. "$(dirname "$0")/_/husky.sh"

# 1. TypeScript strict check
npx tsc --noEmit

# 2. Lint
npm run lint

# 3. Tests (fast subset)
npm run test:unit

# 4. TrustChain integrity
node scripts/verify-trustchain.js

# 5. No Math.random in payment paths
! grep -r "Math.random" --include="*.ts" src/payments src/crypto 2>/dev/null

# 6. Zod schemas for all public APIs
node scripts/check-zod-coverage.js

# 7. Chronicle commit message format
node scripts/check-chronicle-format.js "$1"
```

---

## 🚫 FORBIDDEN PATTERNS (Auto-Reject)

| Pattern | Reason | Alternative |
|---------|--------|-------------|
| `as any` / `as unknown as` | Defeats strict TS | Proper typing, type guards |
| `Math.random()` in auth/payments | Predictable entropy | `crypto.randomBytes()` |
| `console.log` in production | Leaks secrets | Structured logging |
| `try { } catch { }` (empty) | Swallows errors | Proper error handling |
| `TODO:` without issue ref | Untracked debt | `TODO(#123):` |
| Hardcoded secrets | Security | Env vars / secret manager |
| `any[]` / `Record<string, any>` | Type safety | Discriminated unions |
| Mutating props/state directly | Immutability | Immutable patterns |

---

## ✅ REQUIRED PATTERNS

| Pattern | Where |
|---------|-------|
| `strict: true` in tsconfig.json | Root |
| Zod schema for every API input | All routes |
| TrustChain.append(action, intention) | Every mutation |
| Circuit breaker per LLM provider | All model calls |
| `await waitUntil()` for background work | Vercel functions |
| `typeof window !== 'undefined'` guard | Pi SDK usage |
| `determineSandboxMode()` dynamic | Pi SDK config |
| Bilingual `t(en, ar)` helper | All UI text |

