## 📋 WORKFLOW: PLAN → EXECUTE → REVIEW

When user requests a complex task:

1. **PLAN** (Frontier model: Claude 3.5 Sonnet / GPT-4o / Gemini 1.5 Pro)
   - Read full codebase context
   - Produce SPEC.md with architecture, tasks, acceptance criteria
   - Human approval gate (optional)

2. **EXECUTE** (Efficient model: Groq Llama 3.3 70B / DeepSeek V3 / Cursor Composer)
   - Implement per spec
   - High output tokens, low cost
   - Run tests, lint

3. **REVIEW** (Frontier model: GPT-4o / Claude 3.5 Sonnet)
   - Security audit
   - Spec compliance
   - Test coverage
   - Output: Review report with verdict

**Token Economics**: ~60-70% cost savings vs single-model approach

